<br>
(On one port with a wizzy friend, I got to see, in that slow-mo frame update thing that happens when you zone, I saw the familiar die, with &lt;wizzyname's familiar's corpse&gt; on its dead body.  I expect normally that happens so fast its never drawn).<br>
<br>
So, in principle, with the now max-level pets, Verant could allow us to keep our pets on zoning, if they came up with a workaround for the naming issue, but it would be like warders, where we would start with an empty pet.  Its not really that much of an issue I think (its not like malachite costs <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> that</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> much <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) although it would definitely be nice (and probably unbalancing) to have Jobober there as soon as you appear in a new zone, ready to defend you with his life.<br>
<br>
That said, being able to permanently name pets would be a lot of fun!  I'd have to call mine Oopssorrymaster...<br>
